It is very simple to pass data to the component function - you can pass any data you want from the template. You can pass the `i` or `not` if you like.

```
// template
(toggleChange)=&quot;onToggleChange(i, not)&quot;
```

```
// component
onToggleChange(i: number, not) {

}
```

Note: `toggleChange` does not emit `$event`. Maybe you want to use `(change)` which emits type `MatSlideToggleChange` - [API docs](https://material.angular.io/components/slide-toggle/api)

```
// template
(change)=&quot;onToggleChange($event, i, not)&quot;
```

```
// component
onToggleChange(event: MatSlideToggleChange, i: number, not) {

}
```

